.TH SIMPLE_SHELL (1)

.SH NAME
.B
Simple shell (./hsh)
- A basic version of Unix system shell.

.SH SYNOPSIS
#include <stdlib.h> 
.PP
#include <stdio.h>
.PP
#include <string.h>
.PP
#include <unistd.h>
.PP
#include <sys/stat.h>
.PP
#include <sys/stat.h>
.PP
#include <sys/wait.h> 
.PP
.B
.SH DESCRIPTION
- The simple shell project is the final project of the first trimester of the career Software Engineering at Holberton School. to create it we search a lot of information on the internet and apply our knoledge about C programming language.
.PP
- Shell is a programm that provides an interface to the Unix command interpetre system.
.PP
- Takes the user input entered through the keyboard and displays the output in the screen working with the standard input.

.SH SIMPLE SHELL FUNCTIONALITIES
-  Display a prompt and wait for the user to type a command. A command line always ends with a new line
.sp 1
-  The prompt is displayed again each time a command has been executed
.sp 1
-  If a command cannot be found, it prints an error message and displays the prompt again
.sp 1
-  Handle errors
.sp 1
-  Handle the “end of file” condition (Ctrl+D)
.sp 1
-  Handle command lines with arguments
.sp 1
-  Handle the PATH
.sp 1
-  Handle the exit, the cd and env built-in
.PP
Compile the files in the following way:
.PP
.B
 - gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic -std=gnu89 *.c -o hsh

.SH USAGE EXAMPLES
To activate 
interactive mode
write "./hsh". The prompt will be displayed. You can write commands and will be executed by the simple shell. Examples: "pwd"

non-interactive shell
write "echo (
.I
command to be executed
) | ./hsh". EXAMPLES: "echo "Hello!" | ./hsh" or "echo "ls -ltr | ./hsh"

